The issue is in the `canInlineReferenceDirectly` method. When checking if inlining is safe, the code has a logic flaw in the loop that checks function parameters and call arguments:

```java
while (cArg != null || fnParam != null) {
  if (fnParam != null) {
    if (cArg != null) {
      if (NodeUtil.mayEffectMutableState(cArg, compiler)
